  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Residential vs commercial trash compactor — disambiguation</h2>
    <p>Viking residential trash compactor (VGCC / VTCP 15-inch, 1.4 cubic foot chamber, household-scale daily-bag compaction in a built-in kitchen) is a different product category from commercial trash chute compactors (10+ cubic yard capacity, apartment-building or multi-unit residential chute-fed installations, industrial waste-management scale) and commercial industrial waste balers (manufacturing + distribution-center scrap + recycling scale). Our SDAR service scope covers residential only — we don't service commercial trash chute compactors or industrial waste balers, and we will not take on work in that scope rather than risk mishandling equipment we don't specialize in. If your situation is commercial-scale (multi-unit apartment building trash chute compactor, industrial waste baler, commercial kitchen high-volume compactor), please search for commercial-specialist service rather than a residential appliance-repair company.</p>
    <p>Viking brand crosses this residential / commercial boundary as a corporate entity — Middleby owns both Viking Residential (our scope) and Viking Commercial (a separate commercial foodservice division with different product lines, different parts catalogs, different service network). The two do not share parts or service infrastructure. If someone tells you "Viking makes commercial trash compactors" that refers to a product category that doesn't exist — Viking Residential makes built-in residential trash compactors; Viking Commercial makes commercial cooking equipment. This page covers Viking Residential only.</p>
  </div></section>

